3:["$","p",null,{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed","children":"Hyperliquid calculates funding rates every hour using a time-weighted average price mechanism between the perpetual and mark price. The on-chain settlement ensures transparent rate calculations without centralized intervention. Funding payments occur automatically at each hourly interval, with rates typically ranging from -0.01% to +0.05% per hour during normal market conditions. The DEX's sub-second finality allows for precise entry and exit timing around funding settlements."}]
4:["$","section",null,{"className":"mb-10","children":[["$","h2",null,{"className":"text-2xl font-extrabold tracking-tight text-foreground mt-12 mb-4","style":{"fontFamily":"var(--font-montserrat), sans-serif"},"children":["Why ","APT","/","USDT","?"]}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed","children":"APT/USDT presents compelling funding arbitrage opportunities due to Aptos' growing DeFi ecosystem and institutional adoption patterns. The pair often shows predictable funding cycles aligned with Aptos network announcements and ecosystem developments. Mid-tier volume provides sufficient liquidity for arbitrage positions while maintaining attractive rate spreads."}]]}]
5:["$","section","0",{"className":"mb-10","children":[["$","h2",null,{"className":"text-2xl font-extrabold tracking-tight text-foreground mt-12 mb-4","style":{"fontFamily":"var(--font-montserrat), sans-serif"},"children":"Historical Funding Rate Patterns"}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed","children":"APT/USDT funding rates on Hyperliquid typically range from -0.02% to +0.08% per hour, with pronounced positive rates during Aptos ecosystem announcements. The 1-hour interval creates 24 funding opportunities daily, compared to 8-hour cycles on traditional exchanges. Historical data shows funding spikes during major Move language adoption announcements and new protocol launches on Aptos. Weekend periods often exhibit lower volatility with rates converging toward the 0.01% neutral zone."}]]}]
6:["$","section","1",{"className":"mb-10","children":[["$","h2",null,{"className":"text-2xl font-extrabold tracking-tight text-foreground mt-12 mb-4","style":{"fontFamily":"var(--font-montserrat), sans-serif"},"children":"Cross-Exchange Arbitrage Opportunities"}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed","children":"Hyperliquid's 1-hour funding cycle creates arbitrage windows with exchanges using 8-hour intervals like Binance and OKX. Rate discrepancies of 0.02-0.05% per hour are common during high volatility periods. The on-chain settlement eliminates counterparty risk typical of CEX arbitrage strategies. Traders can exploit rate differentials by holding opposing positions across Hyperliquid and centralized exchanges, capturing funding spreads while remaining market-neutral."}]]}]
7:["$","section","2",{"className":"mb-10","children":[["$","h2",null,{"className":"text-2xl font-extrabold tracking-tight text-foreground mt-12 mb-4","style":{"fontFamily":"var(--font-montserrat), sans-serif"},"children":"Risk Management Considerations"}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed","children":"APT's correlation with broader L1 tokens creates basis risk when funding positions across different assets. Hyperliquid's USDC-only settlement requires bridging considerations for USDT-based strategies. The platform's newer operational history means less backtested data for risk modeling compared to established CEXs. Smart contract risk exists despite the platform's security audits, requiring position sizing appropriate to the experimental nature of on-chain perpetuals."}]]}]
8:["$","$Ld",null,{"items":[{"question":"How often are APT/USDT funding rates calculated on Hyperliquid?","answer":"Funding rates are calculated and settled every hour on Hyperliquid, providing 24 funding events per day. This contrasts with most centralized exchanges that use 8-hour intervals, creating more frequent arbitrage opportunities."},{"question":"What's the typical funding rate range for APT/USDT on this platform?","answer":"APT/USDT funding rates typically range from -0.02% to +0.08% per hour during normal conditions. Extreme market events can push rates outside this range, with positive funding during strong bullish momentum for Aptos ecosystem developments."},{"question":"Can I arbitrage between Hyperliquid and centralized exchanges?","answer":"Yes, the 1-hour vs 8-hour funding cycle difference creates regular arbitrage opportunities. You can hold opposing positions on Hyperliquid and CEXs to capture funding rate differentials while maintaining market neutrality."},{"question":"What are the main risks of funding arbitrage on Hyperliquid?","answer":"Key risks include smart contract vulnerabilities, USDC bridge dependencies for USDT strategies, and basis risk from APT's price volatility. The platform's newer operational history also means less historical data for risk assessment compared to established exchanges."}]}]
